{#
The type registries (py_map, init_map, dataclass_init_map, blit_types,
hardcoded_blit_types, uncommon_functions) and the auto-detected
`array_types` list are now built in Python and exposed as Jinja globals
by `generator/common/registry.py`. They are accessed directly by name
inside templates (no `utils.` prefix).

This file only exists for legacy `{% import "utils.ji" as utils %}`
statements; the imports are no-ops now and can be removed when the
templates are touched.
#}
